abstract: LONDON, Jan. 24.--The lull in war alarms which began on Saturday has now become so marked that everybody is congratulating himself on the war scare having permanently ended. This it has by no means done. It may be a week and it may be longer, but a grave recurrence of the panic is sure to come. It seems to be true, however, that the tone of official Russia, for the moment, has become very peaceable.
